rComments: The best psychology prof. i have ever had. Lecture are clear and amazing. Just be prepared to take good notes. Tests are based solely on lectures and the podcasts. Definitely recommended.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures', 'Participation matters']

rComments: She makes everything so clear. Really engages the class with the content and using several different teaching methods. encourages us to connect with other students during class and discuss content, has many demonstrations. gave us all chocolate on the last lecture as a treat, and also to demonstrate how to savour moments. the coolest teach ever.

I was a bit nervous taking PSY220 because I had never heard of her (there wasn't a ratemyprof before either to give any insight) but she's amazing! Her lectures was great (she would also finish earlier than the full 3 hours), the structure of the course was great as her testing was very straightforward and understandable. I loved it!

She's amazing and the class was very interesting. Very easy even though there are a few assignments. She makes instructions very clear and helps you a lot. She also marks very easy, especially if she sees you're trying. I recommend talking to her outside of class, she's very approachable.
Highly recommend this course. She's straightforward, reasonable, and an inspiring speaker. Minimal readings and not a heavy course unlike the other psych courses.
I'm so so happy that I took this course with her, I liked social psychology because of her!!!!! she is an amazing professor ever!! the course is interesting

Such an amazing prof with a great passion for the subject matter. She made the course incredibly interesting for me and made me actually want to learn more by taking more courses in social psychology. Would recommend to anyone that's even considering taking the course, even if not a psychology major.
